The paper discusses the evaluation of research using peer-review and bibliometrics, which are commonly used in computer science research. The focus on accuracy, robustness, validity, functionality, time, and costs aligns with the concerns of researchers in the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
